cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SOC, cs.MM

This paper deals with the analysis of social media data related to cryptocurrency manipulation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which deals with the study of social networks and their impact on information dissemination. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques for bot detection and topic modeling, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses the fraudulent activities related to cryptocurrency, which could be classified under cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
